    "created_at": "2019-04-02T16:39:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-04-02T16:40:58Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": ">  If I wanted to add a new turret upgrade to the gdi tower implementation, each entry needs to have a negative check on every other turret type. The yaml file might get a bit messy as a result.\r\n\r\nThat could be worked around like this:\r\nAdd\r\n```\r\nGrantCondition@PLUGGED:\r\n\tCondition: plugged\r\n\tRequiresCondition: !build-incomplete && !tower.vulcan && !tower.rocket && !tower.sam && !tower.yourturretupgrade\r\n```\r\nto the actor, and change the `Requirements` for all turrets to just `!plugged`."
